com.launchdarkly.client

Class TestFeatureStore

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.launchdarkly.client.InMemoryFeatureStore
      • com.launchdarkly.client.TestFeatureStore
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    FeatureStore, java.io.Closeable, java.lang.AutoCloseable

    public class TestFeatureStore
extends InMemoryFeatureStore
    A decorated InMemoryFeatureStore which provides functionality to create (or override) true or false feature flags for all users.

    Using this store is useful for testing purposes when you want to have runtime support for turning specific features on or off.

      • setFeatureTrue

        public void setFeatureTrue(java.lang.String key)
        Turns a feature, identified by key, to evaluate to true for every user. If the feature rules already exist in the store then it will override it to be true for every LDUser. If the feature rule is not currently in the store, it will create one that is true for every LDUser.
        Parameters:
        key - the key of the feature flag to evaluate to true

      • setFeatureFalse

        public void setFeatureFalse(java.lang.String key)
        Turns a feature, identified by key, to evaluate to false for every user. If the feature rules already exist in the store then it will override it to be false for every LDUser. If the feature rule is not currently in the store, it will create one that is false for every LDUser.
        Parameters:
        key - the key of the feature flag to evaluate to false

      • init

        public void init(java.util.Map<VersionedDataKind<?>,java.util.Map<java.lang.String,? extends VersionedData>> allData)
        Description copied from interface: FeatureStore
        Initializes (or re-initializes) the store with the specified set of objects. Any existing entries will be removed. Implementations can assume that this set of objects is up to date-- there is no need to perform individual version comparisons between the existing objects and the supplied features.
